1. What (Project Overview)

This project creates a highly available and auto-scaling web application using:

Amazon Web Services

Amazon EC2

AWS Auto Scaling

AWS Elastic Load Balancing


             User
              |
              |
        Application Load Balancer
           /            \
          /              \
      EC2 Instance    EC2 Instance
           \              /
            \            /
            Auto Scaling Group


Step 1: Launch EC2 Instance (Base Server)

Go to Amazon EC2

Create instance:

Name

web-server-template

Instance type

t2.micro

Security Group

Allow:

SSH (22)

HTTP (80)

Connect to instance.

Step 2: Install Web Server

Run:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx -y

Start service:

sudo systemctl start nginx

Enable service:

sudo systemctl enable nginx
Step 3: Create Web Page
sudo nano /var/www/html/index.html

Add:

<h1>Welcome to Nilesh Auto Scaling Project</h1>
<h2>Server is running successfully</h2>

Save file.

Step 4: Create AMI (Machine Image)

Go to Amazon EC2

Select instance → Actions

Create Image

Name:

nilesh-web-ami

This AMI will be used by Auto Scaling.

Step 5: Create Target Group

Go to AWS Elastic Load Balancing

Click:

Target Groups
Create Target Group

Settings:

Type

Instances

Protocol

HTTP

Port

80

Name

nilesh-target-group
Step 6: Create Application Load Balancer

Create Load Balancer.

Select:

Application Load Balancer

Settings:

Name

nilesh-alb

Scheme

Internet-facing

Listener

HTTP : 80

Attach Target Group.

Step 7: Create Launch Template

Go to Amazon EC2

Create:

Launch Template

Settings:

Template name

nilesh-template

AMI

nilesh-web-ami

Instance type

t2.micro

Security group

Allow HTTP
Step 8: Create Auto Scaling Group

Go to AWS Auto Scaling

Create Auto Scaling Group.

Settings:

Launch Template

nilesh-template

VPC

Default

Subnets

2 Availability Zones

Attach to Load Balancer

nilesh-target-group
Step 9: Configure Scaling Policy

Minimum instances

2

Maximum instances

4

Desired capacity

2

Scaling policy:

CPU utilization 70%

If CPU > 70% → new server launches automatically.

Step 10: Test the Project

Copy Load Balancer DNS

Example:

nilesh-alb-123456.ap-south-1.elb.amazonaws.com

Open browser.

Website loads.

If traffic increases:

New EC2 instances automatically start.
